Subject: Offer for Internship — AI Intern (3 months)

Dear [Candidate Name],

We are pleased to offer you an internship position with Omninuera for the role of AI Intern. This offer is for a fixed-term internship and is subject to review and final approval by Omninuera's Legal and Compliance team. The terms below are a draft and may be modified following Legal review.

1. Role and Scope
- Position: AI Intern  
- Duration: 3 months (approximate start date: [Start Date]; expected end date: [Start Date + 3 months]).  
- Scope: You will support AI-related research and development activities, including but not limited to data preparation, model development, testing, documentation, and other tasks as assigned by your Reporting Manager. Specific project assignments will be communicated at onboarding.

2. Work Location and Hours
- Work Location: Fully remote (working in the Bengaluru, India timezone).  
- Working Hours: [Weekly Hours / Flexible schedule details]. Please coordinate your working hours with your Reporting Manager. Omninuera expects regular availability for team meetings and milestone deliverables.

3. Reporting
- Reporting To: [Reporting Manager Name/Title].

4. Stipend and Payment Terms
- Stipend: INR 10,000 per month. This is an internship stipend and not an employment salary or wage.  
- Payment Frequency: Paid monthly, subject to completion of timesheets/reports or other deliverables as specified by your Reporting Manager.  
- Taxes and Deductions: The stipend is subject to applicable taxes and deductions under Indian law. The Company may withhold taxes as required by law.

5. Internship Period and Termination
- This internship is for a fixed term of 3 months beginning on [Start Date] and ending on [End Date].  
- Either party may terminate the internship prior to the end date by providing notice as agreed with HR/Reporting Manager or immediately for cause (e.g., breach of Company policy). Specific notice requirements will be confirmed during onboarding.  
- At the conclusion of the internship, there is no obligation by either party to continue the relationship unless a separate offer is made and accepted.

6. Confidentiality and NDA
- During your internship you will have access to confidential and proprietary information. You will be required to sign Omninuera's standard Non-Disclosure Agreement (NDA) as a condition of starting the internship. You must maintain the confidentiality of Company information during and after the internship as per the NDA.

7. Intellectual Property and Assignment of Inventions
- You agree that any inventions, developments, designs, works of authorship, discoveries, or improvements (whether or not patentable or copyrightable) that you create during the internship and that relate to the Company's business or to work assigned to you shall be the exclusive property of Omninuera. You will be required to sign any documents necessary to assign rights to the Company and assist with IP filings where required.

8. Background/Reference Checks
- This offer is subject to satisfactory background verification and reference checks, where applicable. Any adverse information obtained may result in withdrawal of the offer or termination of the internship.

9. Onboarding Requirements
- Prior to your start date you will be required to provide proof of identity, bank account details for stipend payment, and any additional documentation requested by HR (e.g., educational certificates). You will also complete onboarding forms and sign Company policies.

10. Taxes, Benefits and Employment Status
- This is an internship engagement. You are not an employee for purposes of employment benefits (unless otherwise specified in writing). The stipend will be subject to applicable tax withholding. Omninuera provides no guarantee of employment upon completion of the internship. Any statutory or other benefits applicable to employees do not automatically apply to interns unless expressly provided.

11. Compliance with Laws and Company Policies
- You must comply with all applicable local laws and Company policies while performing your duties. Violation of law or Company policy may result in disciplinary action, including termination.

12. Data Protection and Usage
- You must handle personal and Company data in accordance with Company policies and applicable data protection laws. Use of Company systems and access to data will be governed by Company security and privacy policies.

13. Miscellaneous
- Amendments: Any change to these terms will be provided in writing and may be subject to Legal/Compliance review.  
- Governing Law: This draft assumes the Company operates in Bengaluru, India. Specific governing law and jurisdiction clauses will be reviewed by Legal.  
- Legal Review: This offer is a draft and is pending Legal and Compliance review. Terms are subject to change following that review.

To accept this offer:
1. Sign and return a scanned copy of this letter (or confirm acceptance via email) to HR at [HR Contact Email] by [Acceptance Deadline].  
2. Complete onboarding documentation and any requested background checks.

We are excited about the possibility of you joining Omninuera for this internship and look forward to your response. Please note that this offer is a draft pending Legal review and final approval.

